    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-20T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-20T05:00:00-05:00" n="456"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.51/71</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-20T11:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 20, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.50 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6779. Your 5139, July 12, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d456fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_543">p. 543</ref>.</note> Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName> has handed me the long
                    financial statement by the Chancellor of the Exchequer which follows and which
                    he requests me to telegraph for the Secretary of the Treasury and the President.
                    A copy goes also by pouch. The financial situation has caused greater fear and
                    depression than has before been felt from any cause since the war began.</p>
                <p>All that follows this is Mr. <persName corresp="#p_LAB1">Bonar Law</persName>’s
                    memorandum.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
